Dictionary

About

This dictionary aims to describe all the vocabulary items of the twenty Tinellbian languages, consisting of High Lulani and its descendants. In addition, miscellaneous English neologisms have been added, including proper nouns.

Searching

The search box at the bottom of each page allows one to proceed directly to any dictionary entry. Contrariwise, the search box in the navigation pane runs a general search of the site.

-’a

High Lulani

a

/ʔə/

derivational suffix (verb → noun)

derives an abstract noun from a verb

Derived Terms

cura’a yra time

qacca’a q;ca choice

pa’a pa thought

-ʔa

High Lulani

;a

/ʔjə/

particle

(indicates emphasis)

Notes

Placed at the end of greetings and valedictions.

Often elided, moving the stress of the last word to the final syllable.

Example

nàra → naraʔa → narà goodbye!

’ala

High Lulani

al

/ˈʔalə/

inanimate mass noun

heat

Derived Terms

’alamusa alUs sun’s heat

’alaxuhha alZ;h heat of the fire

puci’ala oCal summer

naffi’ala n;Fal spring

japa’ala jpal haze

cussi’ala y;Sal to feel hot

Notes

these are just about the only terms of this type. Anything else uses the genitive.

Examples
abstract count noun

temperature degree

Notes*

This temperature scale is set with 0 0 at absolute zero, and 495 230 at the triple point of water.

In ordinary use, temperatures between 450 200 and 675 300 are given without the hundreds place.

*Numbers in bold are in decimal, numbers in italics are in balanced sesquidecimal.

-ini

High Lulani

/iN

/ɨnɨ/

derivational cisclass suffix (noun / verb)

diminutive; derives a term of lesser intensity or size from another term; dimdiminutive

Notes

Obscene when added to a noun referring to a person.

Example

maʔu m;u gingla

upstream

English

/ʌpʰˈstɹiːm/

preposition

before

Notes

This term is used for objective time: if one time-travels into the past, then one’s death may well be upstream of one’s birth.

Antonym

downstream

To have a thought slowly rise in one’s mind.

Etymology

pa p to think + mana mn realisation

bitta

High Lulani

B;t

/ˈbitːə/

inanimate noun

time

Definition

the two temporal dimensions

Notes

The first dimension of time is subjective: a person’s birth is before their death.

The second dimension is objective: if one time-travels into the past, then one’s death may well be upstream of one’s birth.

Derived Terms

jannibitta j;NB;t to time travel

Hypernym

calu cW dimension

See Also

’u’ili uiL reality

sufi zF space

maʔu m;u gingla

bunali

High Lulani

OnL

/bʉˈnalɨ/

abstract noun

rhyme; assonance

Definition

to have the same vowels and placement of geminates

Examples

(These are perhaps nonsense words, to demonstrate bunali)

papa / para

kana / lara

biru / kitu

kippu / lirru

Non-examples

biru / baru - different vowel sound

kiru / kirru - different geminate placement

tana

High Lulani

tn

/ˈtʰanə/

abstract noun

there is; what there is

Example
Notes

while this is not a noun in the strict sense of the word, it does act like one when used by itself as a subject. This noun can be used as the base to nominalise adpositions.

Examples

tanadi tnD what is above

tanajimuli tnJUL what is outside

See Also

malu mW there is

High Lulani

D;z

/ˈdisːʉ/

ambitransitive perceptive verb

Used for emotions and loves, often compounded. Such compounds tend to be adjectival verbs.

Derived Terms

diss·samma D;zs;m to feel romantic

gingla

English

/ˈgiŋglə/

abstract noun

planes of existence; ghostly realms

Definition

There are four ginglaic dimensions. These correspond to the seven planes in some esoteric systems, or to otherworldly realms, i.e.: in order to explain paranormal events.

Notes

tsarships are capable of moving through gingla.

High Lulani

s

/sə/

derivational suffix (noun: abstract → animate)

derives an animate noun from an abstract noun

Examples

pucasa ocs optimist

sasa ss introvert

dattusa d;es god

diss·sa D;zs youth

mulisa ULs fool

luxirasa WXrs twin

tuhhisa e;Hs farmer
